{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":715,"text":"For over a decade as a doctor,"},{"time":2464,"text":"I've cared for homeless veterans,"},{"time":5130,"text":"for working-class families."},{"time":7185,"text":"I've cared for people who \nlive and work in conditions"},{"time":11406,"text":"that can be hard, if not harsh,"},{"time":13855,"text":"and that work has led me to believe"},{"time":15608,"text":"that we need a fundamentally different way"},{"time":17553,"text":"of looking at healthcare."},{"time":19787,"text":"We simply need a healthcare system"},{"time":21193,"text":"that moves beyond just looking at the symptoms"},{"time":23294,"text":"that bring people into clinics,"},{"time":24973,"text":"but instead actually is able to look"},{"time":27850,"text":"and improve health where it begins."},{"time":30445,"text":"And where health begins"},{"time":31932,"text":"is not in the four walls of a doctor's office,"},{"time":34692,"text":"but where we live"},{"time":36102,"text":"and where we work,"},{"time":38321,"text":"where we eat, sleep, learn and play,"},{"time":41473,"text":"where we spend the majority of our lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44900,"text":"So what does this different \napproach to healthcare look like,"},{"time":47568,"text":"an approach that can improve health where it begins?"},{"time":50794,"text":"To illustrate this, I'll tell you about Veronica."},{"time":54601,"text":"Veronica was the 17th patient"},{"time":56320,"text":"out of my 26-patient day"},{"time":58227,"text":"at that clinic in South Central Los Angeles."},{"time":61174,"text":"She came into our clinic with a chronic headache."},{"time":63693,"text":"This headache had been going on"},{"time":64856,"text":"for a number of years, and this particular episode"},{"time":66809,"text":"was very, very troubling."},{"time":69260,"text":"In fact, three weeks before she came to visit us"},{"time":71974,"text":"for the first time, she went to an \nemergency room in Los Angeles."},{"time":75130,"text":"The emergency room doctors said,"},{"time":77597,"text":"\"We've run some tests, Veronica."},{"time":79555,"text":"The results are normal, so\nhere's some pain medication,"},{"time":82267,"text":"and follow up with a primary care doctor,"},{"time":84786,"text":"but if the pain persists or if it worsens,"},{"time":86529,"text":"then come on back.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":88258,"text":"Veronica followed those standard instructions"},{"time":91350,"text":"and she went back."},{"time":93100,"text":"She went back not just once, but twice more."},{"time":96333,"text":"In the three weeks before Veronica met us,"},{"time":98791,"text":"she went to the emergency room three times."},{"time":100940,"text":"She went back and forth,"},{"time":102807,"text":"in and out of hospitals and clinics,"},{"time":104506,"text":"just like she had done in years past,"},{"time":106272,"text":"trying to seek relief but still coming up short."},{"time":109712,"text":"Veronica came to our clinic,"},{"time":111840,"text":"and despite all these encounters\nwith healthcare professionals,"},{"time":114472,"text":"Veronica was still sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117304,"text":"When she came to our clinic, though, \nwe tried a different approach."},{"time":120925,"text":"Our approach started with our medical assistant,"},{"time":123562,"text":"someone who had a GED-level training"},{"time":125609,"text":"but knew the community."},{"time":126959,"text":"Our medical assistant asked some routine questions."},{"time":129080,"text":"She asked, \"What's your chief complaint?\""},{"time":131532,"text":"\"Headache.\""},{"time":133821,"text":"\"Let's get your vital signs\" â€”"},{"time":135115,"text":"measure your blood pressure and your heart rate,"},{"time":137624,"text":"but let's also ask something equally as vital"},{"time":139637,"text":"to Veronica and a lot of patients like her"},{"time":141707,"text":"in South Los Angeles."},{"time":143514,"text":"\"Veronica, can you tell me about where you live?"},{"time":146155,"text":"Specifically, about your housing conditions?"},{"time":147908,"text":"Do you have mold? Do you have water leaks?"},{"time":150361,"text":"Do you have roaches in your home?\""},{"time":152518,"text":"Turns out, Veronica said yes\nto three of those things:"},{"time":154925,"text":"roaches, water leaks, mold."},{"time":157232,"text":"I received that chart in hand, reviewed it,"},{"time":160347,"text":"and I turned the handle on the door"},{"time":161674,"text":"and I entered the room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163666,"text":"You should understand that Veronica,"},{"time":165116,"text":"like a lot of patients that I have\nthe privilege of caring for,"},{"time":167569,"text":"is a dignified person, a formidable presence,"},{"time":170292,"text":"a personality that's larger than life,"},{"time":172125,"text":"but here she was"},{"time":173925,"text":"doubled over in pain sitting on my exam table."},{"time":176760,"text":"Her head, clearly throbbing, was resting in her hands."},{"time":180944,"text":"She lifted her head up,"},{"time":182293,"text":"and I saw her face, said hello,"},{"time":185400,"text":"and then I immediately noticed something"},{"time":186659,"text":"across the bridge of her nose,"},{"time":188331,"text":"a crease in her skin."},{"time":190416,"text":"In medicine, we call that crease the allergic salute."},{"time":193735,"text":"It's usually seen among children\nwho have chronic allergies."},{"time":196547,"text":"It comes from chronically rubbing\none's nose up and down,"},{"time":199303,"text":"trying to get rid of those allergy symptoms,"},{"time":201609,"text":"and yet, here was Veronica, a grown woman,"},{"time":203646,"text":"with the same telltale sign of allergies."},{"time":206435,"text":"A few minutes later, in asking\nVeronica some questions,"},{"time":209380,"text":"and examining her and listening to her,"},{"time":211329,"text":"I said, \"Veronica, I think I know what you have."},{"time":214134,"text":"I think you have chronic allergies,"},{"time":216188,"text":"and I think you have migraine\nheadaches and some sinus congestion,"},{"time":218451,"text":"and I think all of those are \nrelated to where you live.\""},{"time":221989,"text":"She looked a little bit relieved,"},{"time":223733,"text":"because for the first time, she had a diagnosis,"},{"time":225708,"text":"but I said, \"Veronica, now let's\ntalk about your treatment."},{"time":227945,"text":"We're going to order some\nmedications for your symptoms,"},{"time":231387,"text":"but I also want to refer you to\na specialist, if that's okay.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":234920,"text":"Now, specialists are a little hard to find"},{"time":237226,"text":"in South Central Los Angeles,"},{"time":239028,"text":"so she gave me this look, like, \"Really?\""},{"time":241714,"text":"And I said, \"Veronica, actually,\nthe specialist I'm talking about"},{"time":244391,"text":"is someone I call a community health worker,"},{"time":246677,"text":"someone who, if it's okay with you,"},{"time":248318,"text":"can come to your home"},{"time":249100,"text":"and try to understand what's going on"},{"time":250830,"text":"with those water leaks and that mold,"},{"time":252188,"text":"trying to help you manage those conditions in your housing that I think are causing your symptoms,"},{"time":256226,"text":"and if required, that specialist might refer you"},{"time":258318,"text":"to another specialist that we\ncall a public interest lawyer,"},{"time":260810,"text":"because it might be that your landlord"},{"time":262503,"text":"isn't making the fixes he's required to make.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":265776,"text":"Veronica came back in a few months later."},{"time":267903,"text":"She agreed to all of those treatment plans."},{"time":270715,"text":"She told us that her symptoms\nhad improved by 90 percent."},{"time":273761,"text":"She was spending more time at work"},{"time":275627,"text":"and with her family and less time"},{"time":277513,"text":"shuttling back and forth between\nthe emergency rooms of Los Angeles."},{"time":282123,"text":"Veronica had improved remarkably."},{"time":284335,"text":"Her sons, one of whom had asthma,"},{"time":286329,"text":"were no longer as sick as they used to be."},{"time":288104,"text":"She had gotten better, and not coincidentally,"},{"time":290491,"text":"Veronica's home was better too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294166,"text":"What was it about this different approach we tried"},{"time":296010,"text":"that led to better care,"},{"time":299604,"text":"fewer visits to the E.R., better health?"},{"time":303163,"text":"Well, quite simply, it started with that question:"},{"time":305260,"text":"\"Veronica, where do you live?\""},{"time":308251,"text":"But more importantly, it was that we put in place"},{"time":310627,"text":"a system that allowed us to routinely ask questions"},{"time":313197,"text":"to Veronica and hundreds more like her"},{"time":315498,"text":"about the conditions that mattered"},{"time":317357,"text":"in her community, about where health,"},{"time":319195,"text":"and unfortunately sometimes illness, do begin"},{"time":322147,"text":"in places like South L.A."},{"time":323900,"text":"In that community, substandard housing"},{"time":326129,"text":"and food insecurity are the major conditions"},{"time":327670,"text":"that we as a clinic had to be aware of,"},{"time":329492,"text":"but in other communities it could be"},{"time":331220,"text":"transportation barriers, obesity,"},{"time":333300,"text":"access to parks, gun violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336685,"text":"The important thing is, we put in place a system"},{"time":338919,"text":"that worked,"},{"time":340283,"text":"and it's an approach that I call an upstream approach."},{"time":342554,"text":"It's a term many of you are familiar with."},{"time":344227,"text":"It comes from a parable that's very common"},{"time":346344,"text":"in the public health community."},{"time":348663,"text":"This is a parable of three friends."},{"time":351273,"text":"Imagine that you're one of these three friends"},{"time":353440,"text":"who come to a river."},{"time":355020,"text":"It's a beautiful scene, but it's\nshattered by the cries of a child,"},{"time":358380,"text":"and actually several children,\nin need of rescue in the water."},{"time":361357,"text":"So you do hopefully what everybody would do."},{"time":363250,"text":"You jump right in along with your friends."},{"time":365041,"text":"The first friend says, I'm going to rescue those"},{"time":366830,"text":"who are about to drown,"},{"time":368163,"text":"those at most risk of falling over the waterfall."},{"time":370199,"text":"The second friends says,\nI'm going to build a raft."},{"time":372134,"text":"I'm going to make sure that fewer people"},{"time":373934,"text":"need to end up at the waterfall's edge."},{"time":375419,"text":"Let's usher more people to safety"},{"time":376721,"text":"by building this raft,"},{"time":377883,"text":"coordinating those branches together."},{"time":379739,"text":"Over time, they're successful, but not really,"},{"time":382110,"text":"as much as they want to be."},{"time":383012,"text":"More people slip through, and they finally look up"},{"time":385273,"text":"and they see that their third friend"},{"time":386543,"text":"is nowhere to be seen."},{"time":387960,"text":"They finally spot her."},{"time":389391,"text":"She's in the water. She's swimming away from them"},{"time":391427,"text":"upstream, rescuing children as she goes,"},{"time":393800,"text":"and they shout to her, \"Where are you going?"},{"time":395105,"text":"There are children here to save.\""},{"time":396646,"text":"And she says back,"},{"time":398143,"text":"\"I'm going to find out"},{"time":399372,"text":"who or what is throwing these children in the water.\""},{"time":403430,"text":"In healthcare, we have that first friend â€”"},{"time":406329,"text":"we have the specialist,"},{"time":407404,"text":"we have the trauma surgeon, the ICU nurse,"},{"time":409950,"text":"the E.R. doctors."},{"time":410974,"text":"We have those people that are vital rescuers,"},{"time":413515,"text":"people you want to be there\nwhen you're in dire straits."},{"time":416920,"text":"We also know that we have the second friend â€”"},{"time":419179,"text":"we have that raft-builder."},{"time":420874,"text":"That's the primary care clinician,"},{"time":422585,"text":"people on the care team who are there"},{"time":424743,"text":"to manage your chronic conditions,"},{"time":426333,"text":"your diabetes, your hypertension,"},{"time":427874,"text":"there to give you your annual checkups,"},{"time":429280,"text":"there to make sure your vaccines are up to date,"},{"time":431485,"text":"but also there to make sure that you have"},{"time":433150,"text":"a raft to sit on and usher yourself to safety."},{"time":436626,"text":"But while that's also vital and very necessary,"},{"time":438393,"text":"what we're missing is that third friend."},{"time":440237,"text":"We don't have enough of that upstreamist."},{"time":442352,"text":"The upstreamists are the health care professionals"},{"time":444013,"text":"who know that health does begin"},{"time":446300,"text":"where we live and work and play,"},{"time":448291,"text":"but beyond that awareness, is able to mobilize"},{"time":450823,"text":"the resources to create the system"},{"time":453110,"text":"in their clinics and in their hospitals"},{"time":454918,"text":"that really does start to approach that,"},{"time":458304,"text":"to connect people to the resources they need"},{"time":460306,"text":"outside the four walls of the clinic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462980,"text":"Now you might ask, and it's \na very obvious question"},{"time":464648,"text":"that a lot of colleagues in medicine ask:"},{"time":467303,"text":"\"Doctors and nurses thinking\nabout transportation and housing?"},{"time":470449,"text":"Shouldn't we just provide pills and procedures"},{"time":472759,"text":"and just make sure we focus on the task at hand?\""},{"time":474491,"text":"Certainly, rescuing people at the water's edge"},{"time":477337,"text":"is important enough work."},{"time":480454,"text":"Who has the time?"},{"time":481725,"text":"I would argue, though, that if we\nwere to use science as our guide,"},{"time":484616,"text":"that we would find an upstream\napproach is absolutely necessary."},{"time":487349,"text":"Scientists now know that"},{"time":489104,"text":"the living and working conditions that we all"},{"time":491354,"text":"are part of"},{"time":492990,"text":"have more than twice the impact on our health"},{"time":495380,"text":"than does our genetic code,"},{"time":497507,"text":"and living and working conditions,"},{"time":498840,"text":"the structures of our environments,"},{"time":500226,"text":"the ways in which our social fabric is woven together,"},{"time":503695,"text":"and the impact those have on our behaviors,"},{"time":505877,"text":"all together, those have more than five times"},{"time":508190,"text":"the impact on our health"},{"time":509155,"text":"than do all the pills and procedures"},{"time":511164,"text":"administered by doctors and hospitals combined."},{"time":513213,"text":"All together, living and working conditions"},{"time":516384,"text":"account for 60 percent of preventable death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520480,"text":"Let me give you an example of what this feels like."},{"time":522060,"text":"Let's say there was a company, a tech startup"},{"time":524663,"text":"that came to you and said, \"We have a great product."},{"time":526564,"text":"It's going to lower your risk\nof death from heart disease.\""},{"time":529388,"text":"Now, you might be likely to invest"},{"time":531289,"text":"if that product was a drug or a device,"},{"time":534473,"text":"but what if that product was a park?"},{"time":537211,"text":"A study in the U.K.,"},{"time":538767,"text":"a landmark study that reviewed the records"},{"time":540851,"text":"of over 40 million residents in the U.K.,"},{"time":544192,"text":"looked at several variables,"},{"time":546020,"text":"controlled for a lot of factors, and found that"},{"time":548587,"text":"when trying to adjust the risk of heart disease,"},{"time":552670,"text":"one's exposure to green\nspace was a powerful influence."},{"time":555701,"text":"The closer you were to green space,"},{"time":557580,"text":"to parks and trees,"},{"time":558922,"text":"the lower your chance of heart disease,"},{"time":560417,"text":"and that stayed true for rich and for poor."},{"time":563224,"text":"That study illustrates what my friends in public health"},{"time":565544,"text":"often say these days:"},{"time":567042,"text":"that one's zip code matters more"},{"time":569110,"text":"than your genetic code."},{"time":570786,"text":"We're also learning that zip code"},{"time":572235,"text":"is actually shaping our genetic code."},{"time":574670,"text":"The science of epigenetics looks\nat those molecular mechanisms,"},{"time":577887,"text":"those intricate ways in which\nour DNA is literally shaped,"},{"time":580920,"text":"genes turned on and off"},{"time":582488,"text":"based on the exposures to the environment,"},{"time":584682,"text":"to where we live and to where we work."},{"time":587426,"text":"So it's clear that these factors,"},{"time":589283,"text":"these upstream issues, do matter."},{"time":591366,"text":"They matter to our health,"},{"time":593069,"text":"and therefore our healthcare professionals\nshould do something about it."},{"time":595562,"text":"And yet, Veronica asked me"},{"time":597330,"text":"perhaps the most compelling question"},{"time":598289,"text":"I've been asked in a long time."},{"time":599697,"text":"In that follow-up visit, she said,"},{"time":601835,"text":"\"Why did none of my doctors"},{"time":603987,"text":"ask about my home before?"},{"time":606865,"text":"In those visits to the emergency room,"},{"time":609069,"text":"I had two CAT scans,"},{"time":610870,"text":"I had a needle placed in the lower part of my back"},{"time":612827,"text":"to collect spinal fluid,"},{"time":614357,"text":"I had nearly a dozen blood tests."},{"time":615831,"text":"I went back and forth, I saw\nall sorts of people in healthcare,"},{"time":618485,"text":"and no one asked about my home.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":622770,"text":"The honest answer is that in healthcare,"},{"time":624508,"text":"we often treat symptoms without addressing"},{"time":626203,"text":"the conditions that make you sick in the first place."},{"time":629323,"text":"And there are many reasons for that, but the big three"},{"time":631167,"text":"are first, we don't pay for that."},{"time":635767,"text":"In healthcare, we often pay \nfor volume and not value."},{"time":639152,"text":"We pay doctors and hospitals usually"},{"time":640940,"text":"for the number of services they provide,"},{"time":642920,"text":"but not necessarily on how healthy they make you."},{"time":646219,"text":"That leads to a second phenomenon that I call"},{"time":648530,"text":"the \"don't ask, don't tell\" approach"},{"time":649910,"text":"to upstream issues in healthcare."},{"time":652484,"text":"We don't ask about where you\nlive and where you work,"},{"time":654228,"text":"because if there's a problem there,"},{"time":655453,"text":"we don't know what to tell you."},{"time":658349,"text":"It's not that doctors don't know\nthese are important issues."},{"time":661169,"text":"In a recent survey done in the U.S. among physicians,"},{"time":663040,"text":"over 1,000 physicians,"},{"time":664931,"text":"80 percent of them actually said that"},{"time":666743,"text":"they know that their patients' upstream problems"},{"time":668441,"text":"are as important as their health issues,"},{"time":670328,"text":"as their medical problems,"},{"time":672020,"text":"and yet despite that widespread awareness"},{"time":674381,"text":"of the importance of upstream issues,"},{"time":676315,"text":"only one in five doctors said they had"},{"time":678588,"text":"any sense of confidence to address those issues,"},{"time":681453,"text":"to improve health where it begins."},{"time":683301,"text":"There's this gap between knowing"},{"time":684843,"text":"that patients' lives, the context\nof where they live and work,"},{"time":687272,"text":"matters, and the ability to do something about it"},{"time":690080,"text":"in the systems in which we work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691857,"text":"This is a huge problem right now,"},{"time":694191,"text":"because it leads them to this next question, which is,"},{"time":696339,"text":"whose responsibility is it?"},{"time":697926,"text":"And that brings me to that third point,"},{"time":699635,"text":"that third answer to Veronica's compelling question."},{"time":702909,"text":"Part of the reason that we have this conundrum"},{"time":704495,"text":"is because there are not nearly enough upstreamists"},{"time":708250,"text":"in the healthcare system."},{"time":710295,"text":"There are not nearly enough of that third friend,"},{"time":712195,"text":"that person who is going to find out"},{"time":713959,"text":"who or what is throwing those kids in the water."},{"time":716816,"text":"Now, there are many upstreamists,"},{"time":718521,"text":"and I've had the privilege of meeting many of them,"},{"time":720962,"text":"in Los Angeles and in other parts of the country"},{"time":723589,"text":"and around the world,"},{"time":725357,"text":"and it's important to note that upstreamists"},{"time":727785,"text":"sometimes are doctors, but they need not be."},{"time":730322,"text":"They can be nurses, other clinicians,"},{"time":732515,"text":"care managers, social workers."},{"time":734523,"text":"It's not so important what specific degree"},{"time":736475,"text":"upstreamists have at the end of their name."},{"time":738274,"text":"What's more important is that they all seem"},{"time":740030,"text":"to share the same ability to implement a process"},{"time":744455,"text":"that transforms their assistance,"},{"time":746244,"text":"transforms the way they practice medicine."},{"time":748590,"text":"That process is a quite simple process."},{"time":750176,"text":"It's one, two and three."},{"time":752549,"text":"First, they sit down and they say,"},{"time":754200,"text":"let's identify the clinical problem"},{"time":756224,"text":"among a certain set of patients."},{"time":757567,"text":"Let's say, for instance,"},{"time":759310,"text":"let's try to help children"},{"time":761244,"text":"who are bouncing in and out of the hospital"},{"time":763048,"text":"with asthma."},{"time":765130,"text":"After identifying the problem, they \nthen move on to that second step,"},{"time":767641,"text":"and they say, let's identify the root cause."},{"time":770380,"text":"Now, a root cause analysis, in healthcare,"},{"time":774171,"text":"usually says, well, let's look at your genes,"},{"time":775886,"text":"let's look at how you're behaving."},{"time":778344,"text":"Maybe you're not eating healthy enough."},{"time":780424,"text":"Eat healthier."},{"time":781440,"text":"It's a pretty simplistic"},{"time":782835,"text":"approach to root cause analyses."},{"time":784241,"text":"It turns out, it doesn't really work"},{"time":785906,"text":"when we just limit ourselves that worldview."},{"time":788370,"text":"The root cause analysis that an upstreamist brings"},{"time":790471,"text":"to the table is to say, let's look at the living"},{"time":792408,"text":"and the working conditions in your life."},{"time":795760,"text":"Perhaps, for children with asthma,"},{"time":797842,"text":"it's what's happening in their home,"},{"time":799450,"text":"or perhaps they live close to a\nfreeway with major air pollution"},{"time":802386,"text":"that triggers their asthma."},{"time":804210,"text":"And perhaps that's what we should\nmobilize our resources to address,"},{"time":806830,"text":"because that third element,\nthat third part of the process,"},{"time":809203,"text":"is that next critical part of what upstreamists do."},{"time":811734,"text":"They mobilize the resources to create a solution,"},{"time":813973,"text":"both within the clinical system,"},{"time":815694,"text":"and then by bringing in people from public health,"},{"time":818030,"text":"from other sectors, lawyers,"},{"time":819372,"text":"whoever is willing to play ball,"},{"time":821319,"text":"let's bring in to create a solution that makes sense,"},{"time":823402,"text":"to take those patients who\nactually have clinical problems"},{"time":826212,"text":"and address their root causes together"},{"time":828395,"text":"by linking them to the resources you need."},{"time":830937,"text":"It's clear to me that there are so many stories"},{"time":832714,"text":"of upstreamists who are doing remarkable things."},{"time":835200,"text":"The problem is that there's just not\nnearly enough of them out there."},{"time":837860,"text":"By some estimates, we need one upstreamist"},{"time":840443,"text":"for every 20 to 30 clinicians\nin the healthcare system."},{"time":843389,"text":"In the U.S., for instance, that would mean"},{"time":844644,"text":"that we need 25,000 upstreamists"},{"time":846740,"text":"by the year 2020."},{"time":850207,"text":"But we only have a few thousand upstreamists\nout there right now, by all accounts,"},{"time":854317,"text":"and that's why, a few years ago, my colleagues and I"},{"time":856870,"text":"said, you know what, we need to train"},{"time":858787,"text":"and make more upstreamists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860760,"text":"So we decided to start an organization"},{"time":862466,"text":"called Health Begins,"},{"time":864684,"text":"and Health Begins simply does that:"},{"time":866430,"text":"We train upstreamists."},{"time":867390,"text":"And there are a lot of measures\nthat we use for our success,"},{"time":869328,"text":"but the main thing that we're interested in"},{"time":870689,"text":"is making sure that we're changing"},{"time":872601,"text":"the sense of confidence,"},{"time":874140,"text":"that \"don't ask, don't tell\" metric among clinicians."},{"time":876045,"text":"We're trying to make sure that clinicians,"},{"time":878344,"text":"and therefore their systems that they work in"},{"time":880284,"text":"have the ability, the confidence"},{"time":882579,"text":"to address the problems in the living"},{"time":885254,"text":"and working conditions in our lives."},{"time":888261,"text":"We're seeing nearly a tripling"},{"time":890240,"text":"of that confidence in our work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891821,"text":"It's remarkable,"},{"time":893124,"text":"but I'll tell you the most compelling part"},{"time":895038,"text":"of what it means to be working"},{"time":896607,"text":"with upstreamists to gather them together."},{"time":901090,"text":"What is most compelling is that every day,"},{"time":903413,"text":"every week, I hear stories just like Veronica's."},{"time":907184,"text":"There are stories out there of Veronica"},{"time":909662,"text":"and many more like her,"},{"time":911581,"text":"people who are coming to the healthcare system"},{"time":913462,"text":"and getting a glimpse of what it feels like"},{"time":914840,"text":"to be part of something that works,"},{"time":917400,"text":"a health care system that stops\nbouncing you back and forth"},{"time":919873,"text":"but actually improves your health,"},{"time":921694,"text":"listens to you who you are,"},{"time":922821,"text":"addresses the context of your life,"},{"time":925124,"text":"whether you're rich or poor or middle class."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929489,"text":"These stories are compelling because"},{"time":931144,"text":"not only do they tell us that we're this close"},{"time":933124,"text":"to getting the healthcare system that we want,"},{"time":935710,"text":"but that there's something\nthat we can all do to get there."},{"time":938459,"text":"Doctors and nurses can get better at asking"},{"time":940321,"text":"about the context of patients' lives,"},{"time":942165,"text":"not simply because it's better bedside manner,"},{"time":944676,"text":"but frankly, because it's a better standard of care."},{"time":947758,"text":"Healthcare systems and payers"},{"time":950100,"text":"can start to bring in public health agencies"},{"time":952890,"text":"and departments and say,"},{"time":954305,"text":"let's look at our data together."},{"time":955843,"text":"Let's see if we can discover some patterns\nin our data about our patients' lives"},{"time":959369,"text":"and see if we can identify an upstream cause,"},{"time":961840,"text":"and then, as importantly, can we align the resources"},{"time":964401,"text":"to be able to address them?"},{"time":966737,"text":"Medical schools, nursing schools,"},{"time":968131,"text":"all sorts of health professional education programs"},{"time":970427,"text":"can help by training the\nnext generation of upstreamists."},{"time":974183,"text":"We can also make sure that these schools"},{"time":975938,"text":"certify a backbone of the upstream approach,"},{"time":979166,"text":"and that's the community health worker."},{"time":981361,"text":"We need many more of them\nin the healthcare system"},{"time":982880,"text":"if we're truly going to have it be effective,"},{"time":985233,"text":"to move from a sickcare system"},{"time":986740,"text":"to a healthcare system."},{"time":988238,"text":"But finally, and perhaps most importantly,"},{"time":990286,"text":"what do we do? What do we do as patients?"},{"time":992845,"text":"We can start by simply going to our doctors"},{"time":995110,"text":"and our nurses, to our clinics,"},{"time":996819,"text":"and asking, \"Is there something in where I live"},{"time":999151,"text":"and where I work that I should be aware of?\""},{"time":1001494,"text":"Are there barriers to health that I'm just not aware of,"},{"time":1004342,"text":"and more importantly, if there are barriers"},{"time":1006300,"text":"that I'm surfacing, if I'm coming to you"},{"time":1008281,"text":"and I'm saying I think have a problem with"},{"time":1010400,"text":"my apartment or at my workplace"},{"time":1012503,"text":"or I don't have access to transportation,"},{"time":1014699,"text":"or there's a park that's way too far,"},{"time":1016330,"text":"so sorry doctor, I can't take your advice"},{"time":1018190,"text":"to go and jog,"},{"time":1020276,"text":"if those problems exist,"},{"time":1022157,"text":"then doctor, are you willing to listen?"},{"time":1025453,"text":"And what can we do together"},{"time":1026866,"text":"to improve my health where it begins?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029436,"text":"If we're all able to do this work,"},{"time":1031880,"text":"doctors and healthcare systems,"},{"time":1033419,"text":"payers, and all of us together,"},{"time":1035499,"text":"we'll realize something about health."},{"time":1037693,"text":"Health is not just a personal\nresponsibility or phenomenon."},{"time":1041115,"text":"Health is a common good."},{"time":1044617,"text":"It comes from our personal investment in knowing"},{"time":1046535,"text":"that our lives matter,"},{"time":1048816,"text":"the context of where we live and where we work,"},{"time":1050944,"text":"eat, and sleep, matter,"},{"time":1052680,"text":"and that what we do for ourselves,"},{"time":1054304,"text":"we also should do for those"},{"time":1056424,"text":"whose living and working conditions"},{"time":1058440,"text":"again, can be hard, if not harsh."},{"time":1061058,"text":"We can all invest in making sure that we improve"},{"time":1063544,"text":"the allocation of resources upstream,"},{"time":1065794,"text":"but at the same time work together"},{"time":1067977,"text":"and show that we can move healthcare"},{"time":1070710,"text":"upstream."},{"time":1072747,"text":"We can improve health where it begins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075820,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077847,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}